<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="arbitrary-adj">arbitrary <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ɑːbɪtrəri/    美 /'ɑːrbətreri/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>专横的；武断的；任意的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an arbitrary decision
武断的决定</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The choice of poems wasn’t arbitrary but specially chosen.
这些诗的选择并不是随意的，而是经过精挑细选的。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 6</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>People complain that decisions to approve or deny a permit are often <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ （随意的）rather than based on fixed criteria.  （2013 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. arbitrary  </p></div>